## Todo Item Data Model

### Database Schema (`todos` table — SQLite)

| Column | Type | Constraints |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | `INTEGER` | `PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT` |
| `text` | `TEXT` | `NOT NULL` |
| `completed` | `INTEGER` | `NOT NULL DEFAULT 0` (0 = false, 1 = true) |
| `priority` | `TEXT` | `NOT NULL DEFAULT 'medium'` — valid values: `'low'`, `'medium'`, `'high'` |
| `created_at` | `TEXT` | `NOT NULL DEFAULT (datetime('now'))` — ISO datetime string |

### TypeScript Shape (shared client/server)

```typescript
interface Todo {
  id: number
  text: string
  completed: 0 | 1
  priority: 'low' | 'medium' | 'high'
  created_at: string
}
```

Todos are always returned ordered by `created_at DESC`. There is no soft-delete — `DELETE` removes the row permanently.

---

## Frontend Components

### Rendering

- **`App` (`client/src/App.tsx`)** — root; owns the `todos` state array, fetches all todos on mount.
- **`TodoList` (`client/src/components/TodoList.tsx`)** — iterates the array and renders a `<TodoItem>` per entry; shows "No todos yet" when empty.
- **`TodoItem` (`client/src/components/TodoItem.tsx`)** — renders the checkbox, text, priority badge (color-coded pill), and delete button for a single todo.

### Mutation

| Component | Mutation |
|---|---|
| **`TodoInput`** (`TodoInput.tsx`) | **Create** — text field + priority select + submit; calls `onSubmit(text, priority)` |
| **`TodoItem`** | **Update (toggle)** — checkbox calls `onUpdate(id, { completed: 0\|1 })` |
| **`TodoItem`** | **Update (text edit)** — double-click enters inline edit mode; blur/Enter saves, Escape cancels |
| **`TodoItem`** | **Delete** — delete button calls `onDelete(id)` |

All mutations flow through handlers (`handleCreate`, `handleUpdate`, `handleDelete`) defined in `App`, which delegate to the typed API wrappers in `client/src/lib/api.ts`.

