**Backend API** (`/api/todos`):
- `GET /api/todos` — list all, ordered newest first
- `POST /api/todos` — create (requires `text`; `priority` defaults to `medium`)
- `PATCH /api/todos/:id` — partial update (text, completed, priority)
- `DELETE /api/todos/:id` — permanent delete

---

## Data Model

A single SQLite table `todos`:

| Column | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | INTEGER PK | auto-increment |
| `text` | TEXT | required |
| `completed` | INTEGER | `0` = false, `1` = true |
| `priority` | TEXT | `'low'` / `'medium'` / `'high'`, default `'medium'` |
| `created_at` | TEXT | ISO datetime, auto-set |

In tests the database runs in-memory (`:memory:`); in dev/prod it persists to `todos.db`.

